                        <h2 class="text-center mt-0">TRADUCO / I TRANSLATE MANZONI<a href="#traduco_note">*</a></h2>
                        <hr class="divider" />
                        <p>Thanks to an algorithm that allows the automatic creation of multilingual 
                            digital editions of literary works using neural models (<a href="https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-3834/paper128.pdf">Levchenko 2024</a>), 
                            the project offers access to <a href="./traduzione">fifteen translations</a> of the novel in French, English, German, Spanish, Dutch, Polish, Russian and Chinese. 
                            These translations can be viewed individually or in parallel, in order to simultaneously compare translation choices relating to the same portions of the text.
                             </p>
                        <p>Many thanks to Zhang Shihua and Michael Moore, for generously permitting the reproduction of <i>Introduction</i> 
                            and <i>Chapter I</i> of the Chinese and English translations. </p>
                        <p id="traduco_note">*The project is under development and currently includes fifteen translations of the work: 
                            six complete translations and nine containing the <i>Introduction</i> and <i>Chapter I</i>.  
                            This section will be progressively updated with new chapters of existing translations and new translations. 
                            For details on available chapters for each translation, please consult the <a href="./traduzione">translations index</a>.
                            </p>

                        </p>
                        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-intro" href="./traduco">Go to Traduco</a>

